{# ── Book ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
<section class="public-book">
  <div class="public-book-inner">
    <div class="public-book-eyebrow">Free non-fiction book</div>
    <div class="public-book-layout">
      <div class="public-book-text">
        <h2 class="public-book-title">50 Myths About AI and Data</h2>
        <p class="public-book-authors">Ed. Marianne Mäkelin, Elisa Silvennoinen &amp; Kati Mäkitalo — Vastapaino 2025</p>
        <p class="public-book-desc">
          AI is neither magic nor doom — but it is full of myths. This non-fiction book debunks 50 common misconceptions about AI and data, drawing on research evidence. Written by 30 experts from four universities — spanning computer science, law, education, sociology and philosophy.
        </p>
        <p class="public-book-desc">
          The book was produced in collaboration between the Generation AI and DataLit projects and is available to download for free.
        </p>
        <div class="public-book-myths">
          <p class="public-book-myths-label">Examples of myths addressed:</p>
          <ul class="public-book-myths-list">
            <li>AI cannot be creative</li>
            <li>Using AI weakens thinking skills</li>
            <li>AI is the new oil</li>
            <li>Data speaks for itself</li>
            <li>AI will replace teachers</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="public-book-actions">
